Halve, peel and finely chop the @Echalion shallot{1}(halved, peeled and finely chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Set aside. In a #mixing bowl{}, combine the @diced chicken thigh{520%g}, @tandoori masala spice{1%tbsp} and 1 tbsp @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat the chicken and set aside to marinate.

In a #large saucepan{}, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} on medium heat. When hot, add the shallot and cook, stirring, for ~{3-4%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and @basmati rice{150%g} and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @water{300%ml} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add a pinch of @salt{pinch}, lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, trim the @cucumber{1}(trimmed) then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Pick the @mint{1}(picked) leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). In a #large bowl{}, combine the remaining yoghurt, half the cucumber, half the mint and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Roughly chop half the @medium tomato{4}(chopped). In another large bowl, combine the chopped tomatoes, remaining cucumber, a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}.

Put a #large frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the tandoori chicken (and its marinade) and cook, stirring occasionally, until the chicken is browned and cooked through, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no it is longer pink in the middle.
> TIP: Don't worry if your chicken gets a little charred during cooking, it adds to the flavour!

Remove and set aside two portions for lunch.

Divide the garlic rice and the remaining tandoori chicken between #plates{}. Serve with the cucumber yoghurt and tomato salad. Enjoy!

When you're ready to pack lunch, thinly slice the remaining tomato. Trim and grate the @carrot{1}(trimmed and grated) on the coarse side of your #grater{} (no need to peel). Lay the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} on a #board{} and spread with @mayonnaise{1}(spread). Top with the @wild rocket{40%g}, tomato, carrot and remaining mint. Add the reserved chicken and roll into wraps. Wrap in #foil{}. Refrigerate. At lunchtime, enjoy cold!